\b\fs30 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b0\fs26 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup (1 stick) unsalted butter, room temperature\
{\listtext	\'95	}3/4 cup sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/8 teaspoon salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons finely grated orange peel\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 large eggs\
{\listtext	\'95	}24 ounces sweetened flaked coconut (about 6 cups firmly packed)\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 ounces bittersweet chocolate, melted\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl360\ql\qnatural

\b\fs30 \cf0 Preparation\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl300\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\b0\fs26 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Position rack in center of oven; preheat to 325\'b0F. Line 3 large rimmed baking sheets with parchment. Using electric mixer, beat butter in large bowl until smooth. Add sugar and salt; beat until blended. Beat in orange peel, then eggs, 1 at a time. Mix in coconut. Drop batter onto sheets by tablespoonfuls, spacing 1 1/2 inches apart.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Bake macaroons, 1 sheet at a time, until golden on bottom and browned in spots, 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely on sheets.\
{\listtext	\'95	}Using fork, drizzle chocolate over macaroons. Chill on sheets until chocolate is firm, about 30 minutes.\
